&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;font color="#c0504d"&gt;&lt;b&gt;DDoS Protection System (Russia):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
DDoS mitigation occurs in the cloud at network level through hardware devices. Through the use of a geodistributed filtration system, traffic passes to the closest filter. This ensures the shortest route and maximum performance. Filtering nodes include Netherlands, Frankfurt, Ukraine and Russia. &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The protection guaranteed is 60Gbit/s with several million packets per second. The total filtering capacity specified by our provider is over 1TB/s at 120million pps.  All popular attacks targeting the webserver (HTTP, POST, GET, HEAD, SLOW etc) and UDP/TCP/SYN/spoofed are easily filtered.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;font color="#c0504d"&gt;&lt;b&gt;DDoS Protection System (Germany):&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Through a combination of DDoS mitigation systems, protection of up to 20Gbit/s and several million pps is offered. Layer 3/4 can be protected and includes all kinds of common attacks (TCP, UDP, ICMP etc) &lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;font size="2"&gt;&lt;font color="#c0504d"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Hardware and Network in Russia:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Our cPanel server runs on Intel Xeon E5-2670v2 CPUs with RAID 10 protected SSD drives.  We have specifically chosen this configuration to ensure maximum performance and uptime.&lt;br /&gt;
Our server is connected on a 1Gbps port and is located in Moscow, Russia in the Fiord datacentre. The network has been optimised to provide the lowest possible latency in major regions. It is connected to multiple private and public peerings such as Transtelecom, RETN and Level3.&lt;br /&gt;
